== Physics Bra-Ket Notation

The bra-ket notation is central to quantum mechanics:

$\bra{\psi}$ is a bra vector.

$\ket{\phi}$ is a ket vector.

$\braket{\phi|\psi}$ is the inner product.

$\hat{H} \ket{\psi} = E \ket{\psi}$ is the time-independent Schrodinger equation.

== Font Commands in Math

Calligraphic: $\mathcal{A}, \mathcal{B}, \mathcal{C}$

Blackboard bold: $\mathbb{N}, \mathbb{Z}, \mathbb{Q}, \mathbb{R}, \mathbb{C}$

Roman: $\mathrm{d}x$

Bold: $\mathbf{x}, \mathbf{X}$

Italic: $\mathit{effect}$

Sans-serif: $\mathsf{Var}(X)$

Typewriter: $\mathtt{code}$

Binomial: $\binom{n}{k} = \frac{n!}{k!(n-k)!}$

Named operators: $\operatorname{Var}(X) = \mathbb{E}[(X - \mu)^2]$

